   114→ *       in a BUILD file. They are a useful way of adding a special dependency. By convention,
   115→ *       attributes starting with "$" are implicit dependencies, and those starting with a ":" are
   116→ *       late-bound implicit dependencies, i.e. dependencies that can only be resolved when the
   117→ *       configuration is known.
