    41→ * RuleFunction} objects for builtin rules' {@link RuleClass} objects), and instantiating those
    42→ * rules to produce targets (i.e., {@link Rule} objects).
    43→ */
    44→public class RuleFactory {
    45→
    46→  private RuleFactory() {} // uninstantiable
    47→
    48→  /**
    49→   * Creates and returns a rule instance.
    50→   *
    51→   * <p>It is the caller's responsibility to add the rule to the package (the caller may choose not
    52→   * to do so if, for example, the rule has errors).
    53→   */
    54→  public static Rule createRule(
    55→      Package.Builder pkgBuilder,
    56→      RuleClass ruleClass,
    57→      BuildLangTypedAttributeValuesMap attributeValues,
